<h2>INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE CLAIMANT</h2>

<p>To complete the notarization of your Surplus Recovery Service Agreement:</p>

<p style="padding-left: 20px;">
1. <strong>Do NOT sign the Agreement until you are in the presence of a Notary Public.</strong><br><br>
2. Bring the following to your notary appointment:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;— This unsigned Agreement (all pages)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;— A valid, government-issued photo identification (driver's license, passport, or state ID)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;— Any additional identification that may be required by your state's notary law<br><br>
3. The Notary will verify your identity, witness your signature, and affix their seal below.<br><br>
4. After notarization, mail or upload the notarized documents per the instructions provided by the Company.
</p>

<h2>INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE NOTARY</h2>

<p>This document requires acknowledgment notarization. Please verify the identity of the signer, confirm that the signer is acting voluntarily and understands the document, and complete the acknowledgment below.</p>

<hr style="margin: 30px 0;">

